					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4006336#post-3740298</guid>
				<title>Some detailed questions</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4006336/personal-log-of-richard-larenz#post-3740298</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 16 Mar 2018 09:39:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>sirpudding</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>348648</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So five saints went in:<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-465011-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup></p> <ol> <li>Lowrie</li> <li>Larenz</li> <li>Fontaine</li> <li>Vasilev</li> <li>MacLaughlin</li> </ol> <p>Lowrie, Fontaine and Larenz obviously never came back but Vasilev and MacLaughlin did? Can I use them in &quot;What the Dead Know&quot;?</p> <p>I also don't quite understand the connection to 3959, is it just that some saints tried to use 3959 to self-erase?</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-465011-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Noting that an MTF ω-0 Revenant Team is four saints, in my version of them. Obviously there is no canon and I am already dead, so you can do what you want.</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
